Here are my two cents:

WILDCARDS

   There are really at least four kinds of wildcards:

    1. Define this RR for EVERY name in the given domain.

    2. Define this RR for every name in this domain that does
       not have any other RRs at all defined.
       (current scheme?)
 
    3. Define this RR for every name in this domain that does
       not have any RRs OF THIS TYPE.

    3. Define this RR for every name in this domain that does
       not have any RRs of this type, but is otherwise defined
       (has some other RRs).       
    

STANDARD PRESENTATION/SESSION/TRANSPORT PROTOCOLS

   Certainly if we were to do a replacement to our Yellow Pages
   service, it would be on top of XDR and RPC.  Even if UDP is used for
   the "transport" protocol, it should do the same kind of round-trip
   estimation that TCP uses to avoid congestion.


MULTIPLE INTERNETS

   It would be nice if "relaying" between internets were supported,
   rather than the current dangerous scheme of putting up fake root
   servers.

  -- WIN

